<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Learn Angular Framework</title>
    <style>
        /* Container styles */
        .container {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: row;
            min-height: 100vh;
        }

        /* Sidebar styles */
        .sidebar {
            width: 250px;
            background-color: #dd1b16; /* Angular red color */
            position: fixed;
            height: 100%;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            transform: translateX(0px);
            transition: transform 0.3s ease-in-out;
            box-shadow: 2px 0 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            z-index: 1000;
            color: white;
            padding-top: 20px;
            margin-top: 100px;
        }

        /* Sidebar link styles */
        .sidebar ul {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .sidebar ul li {
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: left;
        }

        .sidebar ul li a {
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            display: block;
        }

        .sidebar ul li a:hover {
            background-color: #b71c1c; /* Darker red on hover */
        }

        /* Content area styles */
        .content {
            margin-left: 250px;
            padding: 20px;
            flex: 1;
            transition: margin-left 0.3s ease-in-out;
        }

        /* Toggle button */
        .toggle-btn {
            display: none;
            position: fixed;
            top: 15px;
            left: 15px;
            font-size: 30px;
            background-color: #dd1b16;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            cursor: pointer;
            z-index: 1100;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-top: 80px;
        }

        /* Style for code blocks */
        code {
            background-color: #f5f5f5;
            border-left: 5px solid #dd1b16;
            padding: 10px;
            display: block;
            white-space: pre-wrap;
            font-family: 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }

        /* For <pre> blocks specifically */
        pre {
            margin: 20px 0;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }

        /* Hide sidebar and adjust content for small screens */
        @media screen and (max-width: 1000px) {
            .sidebar {
                transform: translateX(-100%);
            }

            .content {
                width: 90%;
                margin-left: 0;
            }

            .toggle-btn {
                display: block;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <button class="toggle-btn" onclick="toggleSidebar()">â˜°</button>

        <aside id="sidebar" class="sidebar">
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#angular-material-installation">Angular Material Installation</a></li>
                <li><a href="#ngx-bootstrap">Angular ngx Bootstrap</a></li>
                <li><a href="#what-is-angular">What is Angular?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#what-is-angular-material">What is Angular Material?</a></li>
                <li><a href="#angular-material-stepper">Angular Material Stepper</a></li>
                <li><a href="#primeng-introduction">Angular PrimeNG Introduction</a></li>
                <li><a href="#primeng-table-layout">Angular PrimeNG Table Layout</a></li>
                <li><a href="#angular-7">Angular 7 | Introduction</a></li>
                <li><a href="#angular-8">Angular 8 | Introduction</a></li>
                <li><a href="#primeng-tooltip-button">Angular PrimeNG Tooltip Button</a></li>
                <li><a href="#angularjs-intro">Introduction to AngularJS</a></li>
                <li><a href="#primeng-menu-methods">Angular PrimeNG Menu Methods</a></li>
                <li><a href="#angularjs-examples">AngularJS Examples</a></li>
                <li><a href="#angularjs-controllers">AngularJS Controllers</a></li>
                <li><a href="#primeng-button-templates">Angular PrimeNG Button Templates</a></li>
                <li><a href="#primeng-treetable-methods">Angular PrimeNG TreeTable Methods</a></li>
                <li><a href="#angularjs-paging">Paging in AngularJS</a></li>
                <li><a href="#primeng-table-contextmenu">Angular PrimeNG Table ContextMenu</a></li>
            </ul>
        </aside>

        <main class="content">
            <section id="angular-material-installation">
                <h2>Angular Material Installation</h2>
                <p>Angular Material is a UI component library for Angular applications. Here's how to install it:</p>
                <pre><code>ng add @angular/material</code></pre>
            </section>

            <section id="ngx-bootstrap">
                <h2>Angular ngx Bootstrap</h2>
                <p>ngx-bootstrap is a popular library that brings Bootstrap components to Angular. To install:</p>
                <pre><code>ng add ngx-bootstrap</code></pre>
            </section>

            <!-- Add more sections for each topic -->

            <section id="what-is-angular">
                <h2>What is Angular?</h2>
                <p>Angular is a platform and framework for building single-page client applications using HTML and TypeScript. It's component-based, allowing you to build UIs with modular pieces of code.</p>
            </section>

            <!-- Continue with other sections... -->

        </main>
    </div>
    <script>
        function toggleSidebar() {
            const sidebar = document.getElementById('sidebar');
            const width = window.innerWidth;

            if (width < 768) {
                if (sidebar.style.transform === 'translateX(0px)') {
                    sidebar.style.transform = 'translateX(-100%)';
                } else {
                    sidebar.style.transform = 'translateX(0px)';
                }
            }
        }

        window.addEventListener('resize', function() {
            const sidebar = document.getElementById('sidebar');
            const width = window.innerWidth;

            if (width >= 768) {
                sidebar.style.transform = 'translateX(0px)';
            } else {
                sidebar.style.transform = 'translateX(-100%)';
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>